\\\\r\\\\nsneezing.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**UV disinfection,**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**FALSE.** UV radiation can cause skin irritation and damage your eyes.\\\\r\\\\nCleaning your hands with alcohol-based hand rub or washing your hands\\\\r\\\\nwith soap and water are the most effective ways to remove the virus.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**Garlic has shown antibiotic activity and may not kill virus,**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**TRUE.** There is no evidence that consumption of garlic has protected\\\\r\\\\npeople from\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\ninfection with the new coronavirus.Garlic is a healthy food that may\\\\r\\\\nhave some antimicrobial properties.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**5G mobile networks cannot spread Covid-19,**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**TRUE. Viruses cannot travel on radio waves/mobile networks. COVID-19\\\\r\\\\nis spreading in many countries that do not have 5G mobile networks.**\\\\r\\\\nCOVID-19 is a respiratory virus which spreads primarily through droplets\\\\r\\\\ngenerated when an infected person coughs or sneezes.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**Pets cant spread covid-19,**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nBased on the limited information available to date, the risk of pets\\\\r\\\\nspreading the virus that causes COVID-19 in people is considered to be\\\\r\\\\nlow. At this time, there is no evidence that animals play a significant\\\\r\\\\nrole in spreading the virus that causes COVID-19. There is a small\\\\r\\\\nnumber of animals around the world reported to be infected with the\\\\r\\\\nvirus that causes COVID-19, mostly after having close contact with a\\\\r\\\\nperson with COVID-19.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**Vitamin-C may prevent,**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**FALSE** Vitamin C is an essential nutrient that can support immune\\\\r\\\\nfunction. However, there is no evidence from the current outbreak that\\\\r\\\\neating garlic or lemon (or other foods for that matter) has protected\\\\r\\\\npeople from the new coronavirus.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**Covid-19 deliberately created or released**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**Fa