\\\n    in control, and are optimistic,\\\\\\\\\\\\\" says Dr. Webster. She recommends\\\\r\\\\n    setting goals in your career, relationships, creativity, play, and\\\\r\\\\n    health.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**[What you can do to address stress]{.underline}**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n-   **[Be active]{.underline}**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nExercise won\\\\\\\\\\'t make your stress disappear, but it will reduce some of\\\\r\\\\nthe emotional intensity that you\\\\\\\\\\'re feeling, clearing your thoughts and\\\\r\\\\nletting you deal with your problems more calmly.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n-   **[Connect with people]{.underline}**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nA good support network of colleagues, friends and family can ease your\\\\r\\\\nwork troubles and help you see things in a different way.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n-   **[Challenge yourself]{.underline}**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nSetting yourself goals and challenges, whether at work or outside, such\\\\r\\\\nas learning a new language or a new sport helps build confidence. This\\\\r\\\\nwill help you deal with stress.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n-   **[Avoid unhealthy habits]{.underline}**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nDon\\\\\\\\\\'t rely on alcohol, smoking and caffeine as your ways of coping.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n-   **[Work smarter, not harder]{.underline}**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nWorking smarter means prioritizing your work, concentrating on the tasks\\\\r\\\\nthat\\\\\\\\\\'ll make a real difference.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n-   **[Try to be positive]{.underline}**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nLook for the positives in life, and things for which you\\\\\\\\\\'re grateful.\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n**Many people also use complementary and alternative therapies to help\\\\r\\\\nto control stress.**\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\nThere are many therapies used to deal with stress, including:\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n-   Alexander technique\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n-   Aromatherapy\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n-   Self-Hypnosis\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n-   Massage\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n-   Mindful Meditation\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n-   Yoga\\\\r\